Well, as usual, I think I'm going to come at an album from a different angle than 95% of you. I have heard bits n pices of Autechre's work, here and there over the years..always classified it as "cool", but really didn't get into it that much, so I never purchased any full length cd's.

When I was listening to avant-garde music in the 1960's I would sometimes wonder what on earth could top it,, what would the music of "the future" sound like? Here is the answer. Autechre is "the music of the future", here and now, today.
